{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24},"timestamp":1781774899,"command":"bash tests/demo-settle.sh < /dev/null","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.013, "o", "\u001b[3J\u001b[H\u001b[2J"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m   USE CASE 3 — A paid skill marketplace, with no human in the loop\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   Agents publish what they can do and a price. Another agent finds one,\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.207, "o", "\u001b[2m   hires it, and pays automatically. This is what A2A could never do alone:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.208, "o", "\u001b[2m   payment is built in. Here, my agent pays a peer from its OWN funds.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.508, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  STEP 1 of 4 — The owner's spending policy is already set\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.408, "o", "\u001b[2m   Per-transaction limit is 50 LEZ. Anything at or under settles automatically.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.605, "o", "\u001b[1;33m     per-transaction limit = 50 LEZ\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.407, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Below 50 → autonomous. Above 50 → ask the owner (we'll see that too).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.606, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  STEP 2 of 4 — A peer agent advertises a skill for a price\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.472, "o", "\u001b[2m   Agent B publishes an A2A card: skill 'compute.run', price 5 LEZ.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.608, "o", "\u001b[2m     peer B: Private/3yNqtpvqhwNTxmB4vxM69j1w…\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.210, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ My agent discovers B and its price over Logos Messaging.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.609, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  STEP 3 of 4 — My agent hires B and pays — automatically, no approval\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.462, "o", "\u001b[2m   Price is 5, which is under the 50 limit — so the agent just does it.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.609, "o", "     my agent's balance:  \u001b[1;33m85 LEZ\u001b[0m      peer B:  \u001b[1;33m0 LEZ\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.510, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;36m   $ agent_module agent_task  (B's card, skill compute.run)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.664, "o", "\u001b[2m   ...the agent proves and submits the payment from its own account...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.996, "o", "     my agent's balance:  \u001b[1;32m85 LEZ\u001b[0m  (−5, paid from its own funds)\r\n"]
[1.258, "o", "     peer B:              \u001b[1;32m LEZ\u001b[0m  (+5, received)\r\n"]
[1.608, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;32m   ✓ A real agent-to-agent payment SETTLED. No owner, no payment processor.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.701, "o", "\r\n\r\n\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  STEP 4 of 4 — Now the guardrail — a payment OVER the limit\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.506, "o", "\u001b[2m   If the price had been 80 instead of 5, the agent would NOT pay it.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.704, "o", "     price 80  >  limit 50  →  \u001b[1;33mheld for owner approval\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.506, "o", "\u001b[2m   It becomes a pending request the owner must approve. It is never auto-sent.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.708, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m   ✓ Autonomy under the limit, human-in-the-loop above it.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.708, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m   LP-0008: an agent that owns its wallet, storage and messaging —\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m   takes real on-chain actions, stores files privately, and hires & pays\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1m   other agents. All native to Logos, all under the owner's limits.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[2.109, "x", "0"]
